# Terraform Cursor Rules

## Structure
- Organize by environment: `environments/dev/`, `environments/prod/`
- Use modules for reusable infrastructure components
- Keep root module clean — delegate to child modules
- Files: `main.tf`, `variables.tf`, `outputs.tf`, `providers.tf`, `versions.tf`

## State Management
- Use remote backend (S3, GCS, Terraform Cloud) — never local state in production
- Enable state locking to prevent concurrent modifications
- Use workspaces for environment separation (simple) or separate state files (complex)

## Best Practices
- DO: Pin provider versions: `required_providers { aws = { version = "~> 5.0" } }`
- DO: Use `terraform plan` before every `apply`
- DO: Use `data` sources for referencing existing resources
- DO: Tag all resources with `environment`, `project`, `managed_by`
- DON'T: Hardcode values — use variables and `tfvars`
- DON'T: Store secrets in `.tf` files — use vault or SSM

## Modules
- Create focused modules: one module per logical component
- Define clear inputs (`variables.tf`) and outputs (`outputs.tf`)
- Version modules with Git tags
- Document module usage in a README
